Services include: Cleaning of premises, Maintenance of green spaces by weeding or manual uprooting, brush clearing and tree pruning, and finally fence maintenance. input: Country: France. Purchaser Name: TOWN OF MAUBEUGE. Summary: Maintenance of Green Spaces: Sambre Edge Gardens & Pole Station. Description: The purpose of this contract is to provide all upkeep, maintenance and management services for the green spaces of the Jardins des Bords de Sambre park. The services include in particular: - mowing and lawn maintenance - maintenance, monitoring and necessary interventions on the micro-forest - maintenance, pruning and training of hedges - maintenance and pruning of rose bushes - maintenance and mowing of flower meadows - maintenance of the megaphorbia - maintenance of surfaces minerals (weeding, cleaning, removal of plant and mineral waste) - replanting, replanting and plant renewal operations - maintenance of perennial beds; maintenance of trees and shrubs (care, pruning, interventions sanitary) - the management and control of invasive exotic plants and invasive plants - the installation, upkeep or maintenance of shelters for wildlife - the recharging or renewal of mulch of flowerbeds, hedges, furniture and play areas. These services are carried out in accordance with the requirements of the CCTP and according to the rules of the art as well as the standards and recommendations in force for the sustainable maintenance of green spaces.. Published Date: 2025-12-11. Closing Date: 2026-01-14. Competition: ICB. Financier Name: Self Financed

output.Summary: Maintenance of Green Spaces: Sambre Edge Gardens & Pole Station
output.Description: The purpose of this contract is to provide all upkeep, maintenance and management services for the green spaces of the Jardins des Bords de Sambre park. The services include in particular: - mowing and lawn maintenance - maintenance, monitoring and necessary interventions on the micro-forest - maintenance, pruning and training of hedges - maintenance and pruning of rose bushes - maintenance and mowing of flower meadows - maintenance of the megaphorbia - maintenance of surfaces minerals (weeding, cleaning, removal of plant and mineral waste) - replanting, replanting and plant renewal operations - maintenance of perennial beds; maintenance of trees and shrubs (care, pruning, interventions sanitary) - the management and control of invasive exotic plants and invasive plants - the installation, upkeep or maintenance of shelters for wildlife - the recharging or renewal of mulch of flowerbeds, hedges, furniture and play areas. These services are carried out in accordance with the requirements of the CCTP and according to the rules of the art as well as the standards and recommendations in force for the sustainable maintenance of green spaces.

input: Country: France. Purchaser Name: DEPARTMENTAL COUNCIL OF ESSONNE. Summary: Management of the Plant Heritage of the Essonne Department (5 Lots). The services under these framework agreements include in particular: mowing, mowing, maintenance of flowerbeds, pruning of plants, collection of leaves, digging, hoeing, supply, replacement or removal of dead or damaged plants, pruning and felling of ornamental and afforestation trees, the fight against invasive species, in accordance with the description and technical specifications indicated in the CCTP specific to each batch indicated below. The consultation is broken down into 5 lots. Venissieux is therefore one of the most flowery towns in France. The city has many parks, including the Louis-Dupic Park (or the town hall), Minguettes Park, and finally, in the far south, the Grandes Terres agricultural plateau. The purpose of this consultation is the pruning, felling, grubbing and manual weeding of processionary caterpillars from the city's tree heritage which extends over 165 hectares of green spaces and has around 7,200 trees. Summary: Supply of Fresh Fish for the Operation of the Catering Services of the City of Lille and its Associated Municipalities of Lomme and Hellemmes. The contract was awarded by open call for tenders in accordance in articles R2124-2 and R2161-2 to R2161-5 of the Order Code. It consists of 2 lots. Lot 02 will result in a framework agreement with purchase orders, without minimum amount and with a maximum amount of €164,000 excluding tax over 4 years.
